odoridis ist dem Band beigegeben.  aThis volume presents a comprehensive review of current research on Classical and Byzantine literature. The studies by renowned philologists address the works of poets, historians, philosophers, and rhetoricians. A particular focus is on Greek grammarians and lexicographers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aByzantine literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aClassical literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aClassical philology, lexicography, grammarians, manuscript studies. 4aGrammatiker. 4aHandschriftenkunde. 4aKlassische Philologie. 4aLexikographie. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aBillerbeck, Margarethe, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMontanari, Franco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTsantsanoglou, Kyriakos, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTziatzi, Maria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2015z9783110438604oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831103876740 cprintz978311035428740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311035434840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110354348423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110354348.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2015  aZDB-23-DGGb2015